## Relationships

### Technology Synergy (bidirectional)

- `ai-platform-webui` <-> `ai-model-event-stock-analytics`: shared Python patterns, FastAPI conventions, PostgreSQL schemas, Cursor skill ecosystem; AI platform provides infra concepts (K8s, GPU scheduling) that inform stock pipeline architecture; stock pipeline provides data engineering patterns reusable in platform services
- `ai-model-event-stock-analytics` <-> `ai-template`: stock analytics pioneered skill patterns (autoskill-evolve, skill-autoimprove, 400+ skills) that became templates; template repo distributes refined patterns back

### Knowledge Distribution (directed)

- `research` -> ALL: canonical merge hub for .cursor/ assets (skills, rules, commands); any skill/rule created in any repo propagates to all others via cursor-sync
- `ai-template` -> ALL: standardized templates (sales, marketing, PM rules, KWP plugins) distributed to all projects
- `github-to-notion-sync` -> ALL: Notion publishing infrastructure available from any project

### Content Flow (directed)

- `ai-model-event-stock-analytics` -> `research`: daily analysis outputs, paper reviews, trading reports feed the research knowledge base
- `ai-platform-webui` -> `research`: architecture decisions, multi-cluster designs, TDD docs contribute to research corpus
- `research` -> `ai-model-event-stock-analytics`: research findings (papers, trends, HF intelligence) inform trading strategies and pipeline improvements

### Operational Dependencies

- `eod-ship` / `sod-ship`: all 5 projects are synced together daily (commit -> push -> pull) via project-registry.md
- `cursor-sync`: research acts as merge hub; bidirectional sync ensures any .cursor/ change in any repo reaches all others
- Slack `#효정-할일` (`C0AA8NT4T8T`): consolidated notifications from all projects

## Cross-Project Rules

- **Skill files** (`.cursor/skills/**/SKILL.md`) and **rule files** (`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`) MUST be written in English; Korean is allowed only inside example user prompts or output templates
- **Commit format**: `[<TYPE>] <Summary>` — types: feat, enhance, refactor, docs, fix, style, test, chore (see git-rules.mdc)
- **Slack routing**: each project has designated channels; cross-project summaries go to `#효정-할일`
- **Output files**: pipeline outputs go to `outputs/` directory within each project; `eod-ship` ensures these are committed and pushed
- **cursor-sync scope**: ONLY `.cursor/commands/`, `.cursor/skills/`, `.cursor/rules/` are synced — project-specific code, configs, and data are NOT synced
- **git-push-pull exception**: `ai-platform-webui` uses `tmp` branch for push/pull; all other repos use standard branch operations
- **Pre-commit hooks**: each project may have different hooks; always run `make test-ci` or equivalent before pushing

